WEBVTT

00:06.140 --> 00:10.600
Captions made possible by
HOME BOX OFFICE

00:10.710 --> 00:14.703
A Division of TIME WARNER
ENTERTAINMENT COMPANY, LP.

01:44.600 --> 01:46.636
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU DIDN'T
ACCEPT THE COMPLIMENTARY MAP

01:46.740 --> 01:48.139
AT THE TRAIL HEAD.

01:48.240 --> 01:50.663
MAYBE BECAUSE I'VE DONE
THIS HIKE 100 TIMES BEFORE.

01:50.770 --> 01:52.408
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO INSISTED

01:52.510 --> 01:54.831
ON MAKING A LEFI'
AT THE LAST MARKER.

01:54.940 --> 01:57.579
BECAUSE THE OTHER WAY
DIDN'T LOOK LIKE A TRAIL !

01:57.680 --> 01:58.874
THAT WAS THE TRAIL !

01:58.980 --> 02:00.743
FINE.

02:00.850 --> 02:03.045
EVERYTHING IS
MY FAULT.

02:03.150 --> 02:04.845
EVERYTHING
IN THE ENTIRE WORLD.

02:04.950 --> 02:06.486
NOT EVERYTHING.

02:06.590 --> 02:08.455
JUST THE FACT THAT
WE'RE NOW TOTALLY LOST

02:08.560 --> 02:10.187
AND I'M TOTALLY
DEHYDRATED.

02:10.290 --> 02:12.724
OH, WELL, IF YOU WERE SO SURE
ABOUT THE DAMN TRAIL,

02:12.830 --> 02:16.425
WHICH YOU WEREN'T, THEN WHY
DIDN'T YOU JUST GO AND--

02:16.530 --> 02:19.328
WHAT IS THAT
DOWN THERE ?

02:21.100 --> 02:24.160
I TOLD YOU THERE WAS SOMETHING,
BUT YOU DIDN'T BELIEVE ME.

02:24.270 --> 02:25.532
YOU NEVER
BELIEVE ME.

02:25.640 --> 02:26.902
YOU THINK I'M JUST
LIKE YOUR MOTHER.

02:27.010 --> 02:28.170
NO, I DON'T.

02:28.280 --> 02:29.645
YES, YOU DO, JUST BE
HONEST FOR ONCE.

02:29.750 --> 02:32.275
OH MY GOD.

02:32.380 --> 02:35.178
SOMETHING'S MOVING.

02:35.280 --> 02:38.488
SOMEBODY'S IN THERE,
THEY'RE TRAPPED.

02:38.590 --> 02:39.750
NO, THEY'RE NOT.

02:39.860 --> 02:41.589
(canng)

02:55.540 --> 02:59.829
MUST'VE DRIVEN OFF
THAT DIRT ROAD UP THERE.

02:59.940 --> 03:01.771
IT'S BEEN SITTING
HERE FOR YEARS.

03:01.880 --> 03:03.973
PEOPLE ARE HORRIBLE.

03:04.080 --> 03:05.308
WHY WOULD THEY
HAVE AN ACCIDENT,

03:05.410 --> 03:07.139
AND THEN JUST LEAVE
THEIR CAR TO ROT ?

03:07.250 --> 03:11.243
MAYBE BECAUSE
THEY'RE STILL IN IT.

03:29.200 --> 03:31.031
OKAY, I'M FADING.

03:31.140 --> 03:32.869
I CAN'T EVEN
KEEP MY EYES OPEN.

03:32.980 --> 03:34.572
I NEED TO GET
A CUP OF COFFEE.

03:34.680 --> 03:36.898
YOU FELL ASLEEP WHEN WE WERE
ON THE PHONE LAST NIGHT.

03:37.010 --> 03:38.204
I DID NOT.

03:38.310 --> 03:39.618
( laughing )

03:39.720 --> 03:41.711
I WAS TALKING FOR LIKE
30 MINUTES STRAIGHT

03:41.820 --> 03:44.141
AND I WAS THINKING,
WOW, IT'S SO GOOD

03:44.250 --> 03:47.048
TO GET THESE
THINGS OUT, AND THEN...

03:47.160 --> 03:49.685
( snoring )

03:49.790 --> 03:51.257
I'M SORRY.

03:51.360 --> 03:52.793
I HAVEN'T SLEPT
IN LIKE THREE NIGHTS,

03:52.900 --> 03:55.357
I'VE BEEN DEVOURING THIS
CAMILLE CLAUDEL BIOGRAPHY.

03:55.460 --> 03:57.621
DO YOU REMEMBER ME
TELLING YOU THAT

03:57.730 --> 03:59.459
MY BROTHER'S GETTING
MARRIED ON SATURDAY ?

03:59.570 --> 04:01.731
YES, TO THE WOMAN
WITH NO CHIN.

04:01.840 --> 04:05.207
THAT'S RIGHT, SO I DIDN'T
TOTALLY BORE YOU.

04:05.310 --> 04:07.733
I KNOW IT'S KIND
OF LAST MINUTE,

04:07.840 --> 04:11.606
BUT I WAS THINKING MAYBE
IF YOU WEREN'T DOING ANYTHING...

04:11.710 --> 04:16.170
UM, I MEAN, IF IT WOULDN'T
BE COMPLETELY PAINFUL FOR YOU

04:16.290 --> 04:18.747
TO COME WITH ME ?

04:18.850 --> 04:21.956
UM--

04:22.060 --> 04:23.152
IT'S NOT A DATE.

04:23.260 --> 04:26.252
IT SOUNDS LIKE A DATE,
BUT IT'S NOT.

04:30.370 --> 04:31.496
OKAY, IT'S A DATE.

04:31.600 --> 04:34.797
YOU WOULD
BE MY DATE.

04:37.710 --> 04:38.836
SURE.

04:38.940 --> 04:40.999
I MEAN, WHY NOT ?

04:41.110 --> 04:43.249
OF COURSE
I'LL GO WITH YOU.

04:43.350 --> 04:45.602
OKAY, IT GOT WEIRD,
DIDN'T IT ?

04:45.710 --> 04:47.143
AND I DID IT.

04:47.250 --> 04:49.480
I HATE LIFE.

04:54.890 --> 04:56.528
( clearing throat)

04:56.630 --> 04:58.928
WHAT'S WITH
THE CHITI'Y CHAT ?

04:59.030 --> 05:00.622
HMM ?

05:00.730 --> 05:02.322
YOU CAN FOCUS
ON YOUR WORK,

05:02.430 --> 05:04.159
OR YOU CAN GOSSIP
LIKE OLD BLIND WOMEN.

05:04.270 --> 05:06.932
IT'S YOUR DECISION.

05:10.310 --> 05:13.939
FINALLY YOU DRAW WHAT YOU SEE,
NOT WHAT YOU THINK YOU SEE.

05:14.040 --> 05:17.009
I LIKE IT.

05:21.520 --> 05:24.944
CLAIRE, YOU AND I
SHOULD TALK.

05:32.760 --> 05:35.820
LOOK, EVERYTHING
I DO SUCKS TODAY.

05:35.930 --> 05:37.227
I KNOW,
I'VE JUST LIKE--

05:37.330 --> 05:39.025
THIS ISN'T
ABOUT YOUR WORK.

05:39.130 --> 05:41.860
CLAIRE...

05:41.970 --> 05:45.565
( chattering )

05:50.880 --> 05:54.611
( laughing )

05:56.790 --> 05:57.939
THANK YOU.

05:58.050 --> 05:58.880
OF COURSE.

05:58.990 --> 06:00.685
OF COURSE.
THANK YOU.

06:00.790 --> 06:02.826
OKAY.

06:04.660 --> 06:07.390
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO BELIEVE THIS.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.559
OLIVIER JUST ASKED ME
TO BE HIS ASSISTANT.

06:09.670 --> 06:11.319
AND I START
TOMORROW.

06:11.430 --> 06:13.591
I DON'T
BELIEVE THIS.

06:13.700 --> 06:16.134
I FEEL LIKE I JUST
WON SOMETHING.

06:16.240 --> 06:18.333
I NEVER
WIN ANYTHING.

06:18.440 --> 06:20.908
ME NEITHER.

06:24.350 --> 06:26.818
UM, I GUESS ANY
OF THESE WOULD BE FINE.

06:26.920 --> 06:31.118
HONEY, YOU ACTUALLY
HAVE TO PICK ONE.

06:31.220 --> 06:32.858
CHRIS, PLEASE.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.882
HOW THE HELL AM I SUPPOSED
TO KNOW WHAT KIND OF CASKET

06:34.990 --> 06:36.457
WILL WOULD WANT ?

06:36.560 --> 06:38.585
HE DISAPPEARED OVER
25 YEARS AGO.

06:38.690 --> 06:40.749
AND I CAN HARDLY REMEMBER
HOW HE TOOK HIS COFFEE.

06:40.860 --> 06:43.829
I MYSELF LIKE
THE DELUXE AEGEAN.

06:43.930 --> 06:46.319
IT'S A LITTLE ON THE HIGH END,
BUT IT'S VERY CALMING.

06:46.440 --> 06:50.035
IT'S LIKE A SLOW,
LULLING RIDE ON...

06:50.140 --> 06:54.577
ON THE AEGEAN,
I GUESS.

06:54.680 --> 06:58.002
I NEED TO SIT DOWN.

06:58.110 --> 06:59.407
TAKE YOUR TIME,

06:59.520 --> 07:03.741
THERE'S NO HURRY, WE KNOW
HOW HARD THIS IS FOR YOU.

07:04.920 --> 07:06.456
HE, UM...

07:06.560 --> 07:10.189
WENT OUT FOR A NEWSPAPER
ONE DAY AND NEVER CAME BACK.

07:10.290 --> 07:13.953
SO, I FIGURED
HE DESERTED ME.

07:14.060 --> 07:15.698
WHICH MADE SENSE.

07:15.800 --> 07:17.461
BECAUSE WE WERE
ONE OF THOSE HORRIBLE

07:17.570 --> 07:20.289
GOT-MARRIED-TOO-SOON-FOR-ALL-
THE-WRONG-REASONS COUPLES.

07:20.400 --> 07:25.463
NOW, I FIND OUT
HE DIDN'T RUN AWAY AT ALL,

07:25.570 --> 07:27.936
HE DIED
IN A FREAK ACCIDENT.

07:28.040 --> 07:31.373
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
WITH ALL THESE YEARS

07:31.480 --> 07:33.448
OF FEELING
LIKE HE DESERTED US ?

07:33.550 --> 07:35.814
HONEY, WE DON'T EVEN
NEED TO DO A FUNERAL.

07:35.920 --> 07:38.184
IT'S JUST
AN EMPTY RITUAL.

07:38.290 --> 07:42.488
ACTUALLY, THE CLOSURE
IT PROVIDES IS QUITE POWERFUL.

07:42.590 --> 07:44.626
AND QUITE HEALING.

07:44.730 --> 07:48.097
THE STRANGE PART
IS WHERE THEY FOUND HIM.

07:48.200 --> 07:51.169
IN THAT CANYON, IT WAS 10 MILES
FROM WHERE WE LIVED BACK THEN.

07:51.270 --> 07:52.669
WHAT WAS
HE DOING THERE ?

07:52.770 --> 07:55.933
WELL, MAYBE
HE GOT LOST.

07:56.040 --> 07:57.268
RIGHT.

07:57.370 --> 07:59.008
LOOKING FOR A NEWSPAPER
ON A DIRT ROAD

07:59.110 --> 08:00.134
IN THE MIDDLE
OF NOWHERE.

08:00.240 --> 08:04.108
I MEAN, DO YOU THINK
HE WAS SEEING SOMEONE ELSE ?

08:04.210 --> 08:05.541
I...

08:05.650 --> 08:07.470
I HAVE NO IDEA.

08:07.580 --> 08:11.539
HE COULD HAVE BEEN.

08:13.720 --> 08:16.211
DIANE, LET'S JUST MAKE
A DECISION ON THE CASKET

08:16.320 --> 08:18.322
AND GET OUT OF HERE.

08:18.430 --> 08:21.149
WILL WAS JEWISH
SO I SUPPOSE--

08:21.260 --> 08:22.568
THE SAMPSON.

08:22.670 --> 08:24.297
IT'S PLAIN CEDAR.

08:24.400 --> 08:26.789
GOT IT.

08:50.730 --> 08:53.654
I CAN FINISH OUT THE WEEK,
IF YOU NEED, IT'S NO PROBLEM.

08:53.760 --> 08:56.627
CLAIRE, YOU GOT ANOTHER JOB,
GO DO IT.

08:56.730 --> 08:58.527
IT'S JUST THAT IT'S
AN AMAZING OPPORTUNITY.

08:58.630 --> 09:00.996
TO LEARN FROM
OLIVIER CASTRO-STAAL,

09:01.100 --> 09:02.533
MAYBE EVEN HELP HIM
WITH HIS ART.

09:02.640 --> 09:04.631
AND JUST DO
SOMETHING MEANINGFUL,

09:04.740 --> 09:06.731
INSTEAD OF JUST,
YOU KNOW.

09:06.840 --> 09:08.000
FINE.

09:08.110 --> 09:09.338
YOU KNOW WHAT ?

09:09.440 --> 09:11.442
I WASN'T CRAZY ABOUT YOU DOING
PICKUPS AND DELIVERIES ANYWAY.

09:11.550 --> 09:12.847
WE HAVE ENOUGH
ACTUAL EMPLOYEES HERE

09:12.950 --> 09:14.417
WE SHOULDN'T HAVE
TO PAY SOMEBODY EXTRA.

09:14.520 --> 09:17.114
OKAY, THAN KS.

09:17.220 --> 09:20.212
OH WAIT,
THIS IS FOR YOU.

09:20.320 --> 09:22.208
IS THAT
A GOOD-BYE GIFI' ?

09:22.320 --> 09:25.881
NO, IT'S A BOX OF BONES I JUST
PICKED UP FROM THE CORONER.

09:25.990 --> 09:27.526
WILLIAM JAFFE.

09:27.630 --> 09:29.029
HERE, CATCH.

09:29.130 --> 09:32.122
JUST KIDDING.

09:37.040 --> 09:38.405
I'M NOT SURE THIS
IS SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

09:38.510 --> 09:39.829
NO, NO,
IT'S PERFECT.

09:39.940 --> 09:41.339
LOOK, WE WERE SAVING SOME
BY USING CLAIRE,

09:41.440 --> 09:43.749
BUT WE CAN SAVE SERIOUS MONEY
WITH AN APPRENTICE.

09:43.850 --> 09:45.442
I'VE CRUNCHED
THE NUMBERS.

09:45.550 --> 09:46.619
YOU CAN
CRUNCH NUMBERS ?

09:46.720 --> 09:47.641
OF COURSE I CAN.

09:47.750 --> 09:49.479
LOOK, IT'S FREE LABOR,

09:49.580 --> 09:51.047
WE JUST HAVE TO GIVE HIM
A PLACE TO LIVE.

09:51.150 --> 09:52.913
HE GETS CREDIT
FOR MORTUARY SCHOOL

09:53.020 --> 09:55.159
AND WE DON'T HAVE
TO PAY HIM "BUPKISS".

09:56.460 --> 09:59.384
AS MR. F.
USED TO SAY.

09:59.490 --> 10:00.991
WELL ?

10:01.100 --> 10:02.453
I DON'T KNOW, I THINK
THIS HOUSE IS ALREADY

10:02.560 --> 10:03.766
GETTING
A LITTLE CROWDED.

10:03.870 --> 10:05.462
YOU MEAN, WITH
YOUR WIFE AND BABY ?

10:05.570 --> 10:07.060
I'M JUST SAYING...

10:07.170 --> 10:09.968
HOW DO WE EVEN KNOW SOMEONE
WILL WANT THE JOB ?

10:10.070 --> 10:12.334
I'VE GOT FIVE SENIORS
FROM CYPRESS LINED UP

10:12.440 --> 10:13.805
DYING TO INTERVIEW TODAY.

10:13.910 --> 10:15.172
I THINK
WE SHOULD DO IT.

10:15.280 --> 10:16.747
ALRIGHT, FINE.

10:16.850 --> 10:18.841
ISN'T SOMEONE GOING TO ASK ME
HOW I FEEL ABOUT THIS ?

10:18.950 --> 10:21.817
AI-TER ALL, SINCE NONE
OF YOU ACTUALLY

10:21.920 --> 10:23.581
LIVE IN THE HOUSE ANYMORE,
I'LL BE THE ONE

10:23.690 --> 10:25.317
WHO IS FORCED TO COEXIST
WITH A COMPLETE STRANGER

10:25.420 --> 10:27.479
WHO COULD KILL ME
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT.

10:27.590 --> 10:28.750
YOU KNOW WHAT ?

10:28.860 --> 10:30.327
SHE'S RIGHT,
IT'S NOT FAIR TO HER.

10:30.430 --> 10:31.579
UH, MRS. F. ?

10:31.690 --> 10:33.851
WE COULD SAVE UP TO
$10,000 A YEAR

10:33.960 --> 10:36.190
ACCORDING
TO MY PROJECTIONS.

10:39.940 --> 10:43.535
I DON'T WANT LOUD
ROCK MUSIC IN THIS HOUSE.

10:43.640 --> 10:45.562
NO ROCK MUSIC,
GOT IT.

10:45.670 --> 10:47.774
SO, YOU GUYS WANT
TO TAKE A LOOK AT

10:47.880 --> 10:49.336
SOME OF THE RESUMES
THEY FAXED OVER ?

10:49.440 --> 10:51.806
ARE YOU KIDDING,
I'M DYING TO.

10:51.910 --> 10:54.708
YOU KNOW, MOM, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO BE A MARTYR ALL THE TIME.

10:54.820 --> 10:56.515
I AGREED
TO IT FOR YOU.

10:56.620 --> 10:59.088
YOU NEED TO MAKE MORE MONEY,
NOW THAT LISA IS A STAY-AT-HOME.

10:59.190 --> 11:00.384
A WHAT ?

11:00.490 --> 11:01.912
A STAY-AT-HOME MOTHER.

11:02.020 --> 11:03.783
LISA TOLD ME THAT'S
WHAT THEY'RE CALLED NOW.

11:03.890 --> 11:04.982
WHAT A TERRIBLE
EXPRESSION.

11:05.090 --> 11:06.899
LIKE YOU HAVE SOME
BRACELET ON YOUR FOOT

11:07.000 --> 11:08.024
THAT WILL RING
IF YOU LEAVE YOUR HOUSE.

11:08.130 --> 11:09.620
LISA'S GOING
BACK TO WORK.

11:09.730 --> 11:10.890
OF COURSE SHE IS.

11:11.000 --> 11:12.319
WHEN MAYA GOES
TO KINDERGARTEN.

11:12.430 --> 11:14.933
UH...

11:15.040 --> 11:18.237
WHY ARE YOU
HOLDING A MOUSETRAP ?

11:18.340 --> 11:19.932
I FOUND A BOX
OF THEM...

11:20.040 --> 11:22.304
REMEMBER WHEN WE HAD THAT
MOUSE INFESTATION YEARS AGO ?

11:22.410 --> 11:24.640
THOSE THINGS
ARE SO CRUEL.

11:24.750 --> 11:28.140
MICE HAVE GERMS,
THEY DESERVE TO DIE.

11:29.280 --> 11:31.282
* BECAUSE IT'S JUNE

11:31.390 --> 11:32.709
* JUNE, JUNE, JUNE, JUNE

11:32.820 --> 11:35.687
* JUST BECAUSE IT'S JUNE

11:35.790 --> 11:37.326
* JUNE

11:37.430 --> 11:39.318
* JUNE

11:39.430 --> 11:42.319
* JUNE, JUNE, JUNE

11:42.430 --> 11:44.796
* JUNE, JUNE

11:44.900 --> 11:47.437
* JUNE, JUNE, JUNE

11:47.540 --> 11:49.098
OKAY.

11:49.200 --> 11:51.339
WELL, LET'S JUST HOPE
THAT BAD REHEARSAL

11:51.440 --> 11:53.772
MEANS GOOD SHOW
TOMORROW NIGHT.

11:53.880 --> 11:56.201
GOODNIGHT,
EVERYBODY.

11:57.350 --> 11:59.170
DAVID ?

12:01.550 --> 12:04.110
WHAT, WAS
MY SOLO AWFUL ?

12:04.220 --> 12:05.084
NO, NO, NO, NO.

12:05.190 --> 12:06.179
IT'S, IT'S...

12:06.290 --> 12:07.552
IT'S GOOD.

12:07.660 --> 12:09.082
IT IS.

12:09.190 --> 12:11.579
BUT I THINK YOU NEED TO STOP
TRYING TO MAKE IT SO, UM...

12:11.690 --> 12:14.056
PERFECT.

12:14.160 --> 12:16.219
OH, OKAY.

12:16.330 --> 12:18.798
JUST TRY TO BE MORE
RELAXED WITH IT, OKAY ?

12:18.900 --> 12:23.462
OKAY, GREAT, WELL,
WE'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW NIGHT.

12:24.810 --> 12:26.334
HEY, DAVID.

12:26.440 --> 12:27.600
WE'RE GOING OUT
FOR A DRINK.

12:27.710 --> 12:28.836
IT'S ONLY
GOING TO BE--

12:28.940 --> 12:32.501
A DRINK,
YES, ABSOLUTELY.

12:32.610 --> 12:35.147
DENNIS CAN KISS
MY LILY WHITE ASS.

12:35.250 --> 12:37.445
I MEAN, IT'S NOT
LIKE IT'S THE MET.

12:37.550 --> 12:39.108
HEY, HE'S JUST
TRYING TO...

12:39.220 --> 12:42.018
I MEAN, YOUR SOLO
IS A LITTLE...

12:42.120 --> 12:44.054
IT'S...

12:44.160 --> 12:45.320
WHAT ?

12:45.430 --> 12:46.579
IT'S PRISSY.

12:46.690 --> 12:49.864
IT'S LIKE A LITTLE
GIRL'S DOLL-HOUSE.

12:49.970 --> 12:51.824
LIKE A KITTY CAT
GREETING CARD.

12:51.930 --> 12:54.592
LIKE A POOFY WHITE
CUTESIE-PIE.

12:54.700 --> 12:56.292
THANKS, TERRY,
I GET THE POINT.

12:56.400 --> 12:58.402
GOD, I WAS JUST TRYING
TO MAKE IT SOUND...

12:58.510 --> 12:59.875
PRETTY.

12:59.980 --> 13:01.607
THAT'S THE POINT,
DEAR.

13:01.710 --> 13:02.938
DON'T.

13:03.050 --> 13:04.574
JUST SING FROM
SOMEPLACE REAL.

13:04.680 --> 13:08.138
( cheering )

13:08.250 --> 13:10.946
GOD, WHEN DID I BECOME
400 YEARS OLD ?

13:11.050 --> 13:13.484
ON YOUR LAST
BIRTH DAY.

13:13.590 --> 13:16.218
NOT THAT YOU WOULD REMEMBER
ANYTHING FROM THAT NIGHT.

13:16.320 --> 13:18.322
HE WAS ACTUALLY TRYING
TO CONVINCE THIS GUY

13:18.430 --> 13:20.853
THAT HE USED TO BE
IN CIRQUE DU SOLEIL.

13:20.960 --> 13:26.091
TER, SHOW HIM THE COMING DOWN
FROM A TRAPEZE LOOK, PLEASE.

13:31.470 --> 13:33.131
I HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

13:33.240 --> 13:34.969
I'LL GET A CHECK
SO WE CAN GET OUT OF HERE.

13:35.080 --> 13:38.538
THIS ONE IS OBSESSED
WITH "TRADING SPACES".

13:38.650 --> 13:41.471
WE'RE LUCKY
WE GOT HIM THIS LONG.

13:45.720 --> 13:49.554
LOOK, I KNOW I'M NOT SUPPOSED
TO SAY ANYTHING, BUT I WILL.

13:49.660 --> 13:52.151
I FEEL WEIRD
NOT ACKNOWLEDGING IT.

13:52.260 --> 13:53.352
WHAT ?

13:53.460 --> 13:55.018
YOU KNOW--

13:56.000 --> 13:57.592
HOW WE KNOW
EACH OTHER.

13:57.700 --> 13:59.258
FROM CHORUS ?

13:59.370 --> 14:01.292
FINE, JUST PRETEND.

14:01.400 --> 14:02.765
WHATEVER.

14:02.870 --> 14:04.098
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

14:04.210 --> 14:06.132
FROM THE BATHROOM
AT SEARS.

14:06.240 --> 14:08.470
IT WAS WHAT, SEVEN,
EIGHT YEARS AGO ?

14:08.580 --> 14:10.969
YOU JERKED ME OFF.

14:11.080 --> 14:12.877
THE SECOND STALL ?

14:12.980 --> 14:15.016
THE SECURITY GUY
ALMOST CAUGHT US ?

14:15.120 --> 14:18.112
I...

14:18.220 --> 14:21.417
HONESTLY, YOU'RE CONFUSING ME
WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

14:21.520 --> 14:22.782
OH, COME ON.

14:22.890 --> 14:24.357
YOU CHECKED ME OUT
IN AUTOMOTIVE SUPPLIES,

14:24.460 --> 14:26.485
I FOLLOWED YOU
INTO HOME APPLIANCES,

14:26.590 --> 14:29.229
WE MET UP IN THE SECOND FLOOR
JOHN WHERE EVERYONE--

14:29.330 --> 14:30.365
THIS WASN'T ME.

14:30.470 --> 14:31.596
OH, PLEASE.

14:31.700 --> 14:35.261
FINE, BE THAT WAY.

14:38.470 --> 14:39.869
IS THAT ENOUGH ?

14:39.980 --> 14:41.231
DO YOU NEED MORE ?

14:41.340 --> 14:44.400
I THINK $40.00
IS TOO MUCH.

14:44.510 --> 14:47.616
SO, DAVID, IS YOUR BOYFRIEND
COMING TO THE CONCERT TOMORROW ?

14:47.720 --> 14:49.119
YEAH, HE'S SUPPOSED TO.

14:49.220 --> 14:52.417
I CAN'T WAIT
TO MEET HIM.

14:56.960 --> 14:58.848
GODDAMNIT.

14:58.960 --> 15:00.552
AREN'T THERE
INSTRUCTIONS ?

15:00.660 --> 15:05.097
A PAGE OF HIEROGLYPHICS SHOWING
NOTHING THAT CAME IN THIS BOX.

15:07.600 --> 15:08.965
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?

15:09.070 --> 15:12.562
I'M CIRCLING PROBLEM PURCHASES
ON THE VISA BILL.

15:12.670 --> 15:15.036
PROBLEM PURCHASES ?

15:15.140 --> 15:18.143
THINGS WE BOUGHT
THAT MAYBE WE DIDN'T NEED

15:18.250 --> 15:21.344
OR COULD
BUY LESS OF.

15:23.620 --> 15:25.941
YOU MEAN
THINGS IOUGHT.

15:26.050 --> 15:28.814
WHAT ARE THESE
LITTLE SMILEY FACES ?

15:28.920 --> 15:30.182
GOOD PURCHASES ?

15:30.290 --> 15:32.326
NO, I WAS
JUST DOODLING.

15:32.430 --> 15:34.022
MMM.

15:34.130 --> 15:36.598
I DON'T SEE WHY THESE
ARE PROBLEM PURCHASES.

15:36.700 --> 15:37.667
THIS WAS LUNCH
WITH DAVID.

15:37.770 --> 15:39.362
I HAD TO EAT.

15:39.470 --> 15:41.438
YOU DIDN'T HAVE
TO SPEND $55.00.

15:41.540 --> 15:42.598
WHAT DID YOU HAVE ?

15:42.700 --> 15:44.008
A COUPLE OF
SANDWICHES.

15:44.110 --> 15:45.964
THIS COUNTRY
IS INSANE.

15:46.070 --> 15:47.674
WHAT ABOUT
THIS ONE ?

15:47.780 --> 15:49.338
YOU DROPPED $80.00
AT BOOK SOUP.

15:49.440 --> 15:51.670
I GUESS YOU HAVEN'T
HEARD OF LIBRARIES.

15:51.780 --> 15:53.372
LIBRARIES ARE
DEPRESSING.

15:53.480 --> 15:54.777
NATE.

15:54.880 --> 15:56.040
YOU'RE NOT
SINGLE ANYMORE.

15:56.150 --> 15:58.311
YOU CAN'T KEEP
SPENDING LIKE YOU ARE.

16:00.020 --> 16:04.423
OKAY, I'LL TRY
AND CUT DOWN.

16:04.530 --> 16:08.990
YOU KNOW, UNTIL
YOU GO BACK TO WORK.

16:11.600 --> 16:15.434
UM, ACTUALLY, I'M HOLDING OFF
LOOKING FOR ANOTHER JOB.

16:15.540 --> 16:16.859
REALLY ?

16:16.970 --> 16:18.562
FOR HOW LONG ?

16:18.670 --> 16:20.729
I DON'T KNOW,
WE'LL SEE.

16:20.840 --> 16:22.273
BECAUSE MY MOM SEEMS
TO THINK THAT

16:22.380 --> 16:25.178
IT'S UNTIL MAYA
STARTS KINDERGARTEN.

16:26.680 --> 16:30.684
THIS IS NOT A DECISION
YOU CAN MAKE WITHOUT ME.

16:32.490 --> 16:34.253
OKAY.

16:45.430 --> 16:46.226
HEY.

16:46.330 --> 16:47.968
THAT WAS
A LATE REHEARSAL.

16:48.070 --> 16:49.594
YEAH, WE JUST--

16:49.700 --> 16:52.032
YOU KNOW, THE CONCERT'S
TOMORROW NIGHT, SO...

16:52.140 --> 16:53.971
OH, WHAT TIME SHOULD
I BE THERE ?

16:54.080 --> 16:57.277
UH, 7:30.

16:57.380 --> 17:00.076
I DON'T GET OFF
UNTIL NINE AT THE EARLIEST.

17:00.180 --> 17:01.670
YOU CAN'T MAKE IT ?

17:01.780 --> 17:04.442
DAVID, PLEASE DON'T TRY
AND MAKE ME FEEL GUILTY, OKAY ?

17:04.550 --> 17:06.848
I DID EVERYTHING I COULD
TO CHANGE MY SCHEDULE, BUT--

17:06.950 --> 17:08.315
I UNDERSTAND,
IT'S OKAY, REALLY.

17:08.420 --> 17:09.455
YOU'LL COME
TO THE NEXT ONE.

17:09.560 --> 17:11.357
BOY, JUST TWIST
THE KNIFE IN DEEPER.

17:11.460 --> 17:13.394
I'M GOING TO TALK
TO FRANK ABOUT THIS.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.695
KEITH, YOU REALLY
DON'T HAVE TO COME.

17:15.800 --> 17:17.665
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL,
I'M NOT ANGRY.

17:17.770 --> 17:20.295
REALLY ?

17:23.840 --> 17:25.102
THANK YOU...

17:25.210 --> 17:27.929
FOR BEING SO AWARE,
THIS ISN'T ABOUT YOU.

17:28.040 --> 17:32.079
WE REALLY ARE
MAKING PROGRESS.

17:36.650 --> 17:39.414
YOU KNOW, THIS IS
REALLY FUCKED UP.

17:39.520 --> 17:42.387
MISSING YOUR CONCERT
FOR THIS LAME-ASS JOB.

17:42.490 --> 17:44.651
I SHOULD JUST
CALL IN SICK.

17:44.760 --> 17:45.920
NO, DON'T.

17:46.030 --> 17:47.622
I DON'T GET IT.

17:47.730 --> 17:49.459
HOW DID MY LIFE BECOME
SO FUCKING MEANINGLESS ?

17:49.560 --> 17:50.959
I USED TO MAKE
A DIFFERENCE.

17:51.070 --> 17:53.334
I USED TO PROTECT
PEOPLE'S LIVES.

17:53.440 --> 17:55.067
NOW, I JUST
PROTECT THEIR STUFF.

17:55.170 --> 17:56.489
WORK ISN'T
EVERYTHING.

17:56.600 --> 17:58.158
I GIVE YOU SOME MEANING,
DON'T I ?

17:58.270 --> 17:59.737
YOU GIVE ME MEANING.

17:59.840 --> 18:01.376
OF COURSE.

18:01.480 --> 18:04.142
BUT WE CAN'T BE EVERYTHING
FOR EACH OTHER, DAVID.

18:04.250 --> 18:06.741
I MEAN, THAT'S JUST
NOT POSSIBLE.

18:06.850 --> 18:10.684
( soft music )

18:26.130 --> 18:28.963
I'LL BE DONE
IN A FEW MINUTES, ARTHUR.

18:29.070 --> 18:30.708
YOU'RE A LITTLE EARLY.

18:30.810 --> 18:33.005
ACTUALLY,
I WAS A LOT EARLY.

18:33.110 --> 18:34.998
SO, I WALKED AROUND
THE BLOCK FOR A WHILE.

18:35.110 --> 18:39.240
AN ELDERLY WOMAN WHO WAS
ALMOST COMPLETELY BALD

18:39.350 --> 18:42.911
TOLD ME TO
GET OFF HER LAWN.

18:43.020 --> 18:44.988
MAY I ASK YOU
A PERSONAL QUESTION ?

18:45.090 --> 18:46.512
YOU CAN ASK.

18:46.620 --> 18:49.350
WHY DID YOU CHOOSE ME
OVER THE OTHER APPLICANTS ?

18:49.460 --> 18:51.655
I'M ONLY ASKING BECAUSE
I'M ALWAYS LOOKING TO IMPROVE

18:51.760 --> 18:53.523
MY INTERVIEW SKILLS.

18:53.630 --> 18:55.052
FAIR ENOUGH.

18:55.160 --> 18:57.765
IT WAS BETWEEN YOU
AND JUDY LINDAMAN,

18:57.870 --> 19:00.634
BUT WE JUST THOUGHT
YOU WOULD FIT HERE BETTER.

19:00.740 --> 19:03.402
BASED ON... ?

19:03.510 --> 19:04.807
WELL...

19:04.910 --> 19:08.801
THERE WAS SOMETHING IN THE WAY
YOU TALKED ABOUT YOUR, UH...

19:08.910 --> 19:11.208
YOUR GRANDMOTHER.

19:11.310 --> 19:13.414
MY GREAT
AUNT PEARL.

19:13.520 --> 19:16.080
SHE WAS A VERY
SPECIAL WOMAN.

19:16.180 --> 19:18.182
I BARELY KNEW
MY PARENTS.

19:18.290 --> 19:21.214
THEY BURNED TO DEATH
IN A FIRE WHEN I WAS FIVE.

19:21.320 --> 19:23.151
OH, I'M SORRY.

19:23.260 --> 19:24.852
MY AUNT PEARL GAVE UP
EVERYTHING FOR ME.

19:24.960 --> 19:26.120
SHE HOME-SCHOOLED ME.

19:26.230 --> 19:27.424
YEAH.

19:27.530 --> 19:29.225
YEAH, YOU SEEM
A LITTLE...

19:29.330 --> 19:31.924
HOME-SCHOOLED.

19:34.970 --> 19:37.234
AH, SHIT.

19:37.340 --> 19:39.865
THESE COLLAGEN LIPS
ARE SUCH A BITCH.

19:39.970 --> 19:44.805
I'M GUESSING YOUR AUNT PEARL
DIDN'T LIKE CUSSING, HUH ?

19:44.910 --> 19:47.447
NOT ONE BIT.

19:47.550 --> 19:49.973
SHE WOULD HAVE TARRED ME
FOR THAT KIND OF LANGUAGE.

19:50.080 --> 19:51.945
RICO, HAVE YOU...

19:52.050 --> 19:53.312
OH, MRS. F.

19:53.420 --> 19:55.684
THIS IS ARTHUR MARTIN,
OUR NEW APPRENTICE.

19:55.790 --> 19:56.779
HELLO.

19:56.890 --> 19:58.721
EXCUSE ME,
HAVE YOU SEEN NATE ?

19:58.830 --> 20:00.695
LISA'S LOOKING
FOR HIM.

20:08.240 --> 20:10.504
THAT'LL BE $62.90.

20:10.610 --> 20:13.374
THERE YOU GO.

20:14.840 --> 20:17.240
( beep)

20:17.350 --> 20:19.341
OH, I HAVE TO TALK
TO MY MANAGER.

20:19.450 --> 20:22.214
I NEED
CREDIT APPROVAL !

20:22.320 --> 20:24.538
THIS CD IS
SO GREAT FOR LIKE,

20:24.650 --> 20:28.814
TAKING DIET PILLS
AND CLEANING YOUR BATHROOM.

20:33.300 --> 20:34.790
WHAT ARE YOU DOING... ?

20:34.900 --> 20:36.094
UH--

20:36.200 --> 20:37.519
DO YOU EVEN LISTEN
TO ME WHEN I TALK ?

20:37.630 --> 20:39.393
OR DO YOU JUST HEAR STATIC
EVERY TIME I OPEN MY MOUTH ?

20:39.500 --> 20:41.434
HOW ON EARTH DO YOU EXPECT
MAYA TO GO TO COLLEGE ?

20:41.540 --> 20:43.929
YOU'RE THROWING EVERYTHING
WE HAVE TOGETHER

20:44.040 --> 20:46.258
AWAY FOR FUCKING BECK ?

20:47.380 --> 20:49.735
JUST SIGN HERE,
PLEASE.

20:49.840 --> 20:51.341
YOU KNOW WHAT ?

20:51.450 --> 20:53.475
I DON'T WANT THESE,
I CHANGED MY MIND.

20:53.580 --> 20:57.710
SO, CAN WE JUST
CANCEL THIS PURCHASE ?

21:32.250 --> 21:36.186
COME ON, CLAIRE, THE EARLY WORM
CATCHES THINGS, LET'S GO.

21:36.290 --> 21:39.225
OKAY, WHERE'S
YOUR STUDIO ?

21:39.330 --> 21:40.251
IN MY HOUSE.

21:40.360 --> 21:41.429
WHY IS THAT
YOUR BUSINESS ?

21:41.530 --> 21:43.725
ISN'T THAT WHERE
WE'RE GOING ?

21:43.830 --> 21:44.797
NO.

21:44.900 --> 21:46.720
WE'RE GOING TO
THE CENTURY CITY MALL.

21:46.830 --> 21:47.592
THE MALL ?

21:47.700 --> 21:49.395
BEST MALL
IN THE WORLD.

21:49.500 --> 21:50.728
I USED TO LIKE LIVINGSTON MALL
WHEN I TAUGHT AT RUTGERS.

21:50.840 --> 21:52.467
BUT THEN BAMBERGERS
WENT OUT OF BUSINESS

21:52.570 --> 21:54.606
AND IT ALL WENT
STRAIGHT TO HELL.

21:54.710 --> 21:55.608
WAIT.

21:55.710 --> 21:58.201
YOU NEED AN ASSISTANT
TO SHOP ?

21:58.310 --> 22:01.040
I NEED AN ASSISTANT
TO DRIVE ME.

22:01.150 --> 22:03.482
MY LICENSE WAS TAKEN AWAY
BY A JACK-BOOTED FASCIST.

22:03.590 --> 22:05.615
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I AM ALWAYS PERSECUTED,

22:05.720 --> 22:07.244
BUT IT HAS
ALWAYS BEEN SO.

22:07.360 --> 22:08.918
SO...

22:09.020 --> 22:10.317
I'M YOUR DRIVER ?

22:10.430 --> 22:12.227
YES, CAN WE GO NOW ?

22:12.330 --> 22:13.957
BRENTANO'S IS
HAVING A SALE.

22:14.060 --> 22:15.891
AND IF I EVER CATCH YOU
WITH MY TOOTHBRUSH AGAIN,

22:16.000 --> 22:17.968
YOU'RE DEAD MEAT.

22:27.710 --> 22:30.076
THIS IS MY BROTHER,
NATE.

22:30.180 --> 22:32.171
NATE, THIS IS
TOM JAFFE.

22:32.280 --> 22:34.145
WILLIAM JAFFE'S SON.

22:34.250 --> 22:36.218
OH, I DIDN'T
REALIZE HE HAD A...

22:36.320 --> 22:38.311
LOOK, I'M SO SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

22:38.420 --> 22:40.217
I WAS ONLY
A FEW MONTHS OLD WHEN HE...

22:40.320 --> 22:43.016
WHEN IT HAPPENED.

22:43.120 --> 22:45.520
I NEVER EVEN
KNEW HIM.

22:45.630 --> 22:48.997
TOM WAS JUST DROPPING OFF
SOME OF HIS FATHER'S BELONGINGS.

22:49.100 --> 22:51.523
IT SEEMS KIND
OF STRANGE

22:51.630 --> 22:53.598
CONSIDERING THAT
THERE'S NO REAL BODY.

22:53.700 --> 22:55.292
WELL, IN SITUATIONS
LIKE YOUR FATHER'S,

22:55.400 --> 22:57.265
WE FIND IT HELPS
THE FAMILY TO PUT

22:57.370 --> 22:59.429
SOME OF HIS BELONGINGS
TO REST ALSO.

22:59.540 --> 23:02.600
WELL, I HOPE
THIS'LL DO.

23:05.210 --> 23:09.146
WAS YOUR FATHER
A LITTLE PERSON ?

23:09.250 --> 23:13.118
NO, THIS WAS THE ONLY SUIT
OF HIS MY MOTHER COULD FIND.

23:13.220 --> 23:16.087
IT WAS IN SOME BOX
HIS FAMILY HAD.

23:16.190 --> 23:18.226
IT'S FROM HIS
BAR MITZVAH.

23:18.330 --> 23:21.049
OH, AND THERE'S THIS.

23:21.160 --> 23:22.593
IT WAS
IN THE SAME BOX.

23:22.700 --> 23:24.122
IT EITHER BELONGED
TO HIM OR MY UNCLE.

23:24.230 --> 23:28.929
MY MOTHER THINKS SHE REMEMBERS
MY FATHER LIKING "BLUE BAYOU".

23:33.070 --> 23:36.608
WELL, I'M GOING TO GET FIRED
IF I'M NOT BACK BY TWO.

23:36.710 --> 23:39.178
SO, IF THAT'S ALL... ?

23:39.280 --> 23:43.944
YES, WE'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW
AFTERNOON AT THE FUNERAL.

23:46.350 --> 23:47.715
THAN KS.

23:50.690 --> 23:53.727
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH YOU ?

23:56.130 --> 23:59.019
CAN YOU IMAGINE BEING SO CALM
ABOUT YOUR FATHER'S DEATH ?

23:59.130 --> 24:01.894
WELL, HE PROBABLY THINKS OF HIS
STEP-FATHER AS HIS REAL FATHER.

24:02.000 --> 24:03.297
AS HE SHOULD.

24:03.400 --> 24:05.061
HE DOESN'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT HIS DAD.

24:05.170 --> 24:06.467
NOT A THING.

24:06.570 --> 24:08.629
HE HAS NO IDEA WHETHER
HE EVEN LIKED LINDA RONSTADT.

24:08.740 --> 24:11.538
DO YOU KNOW IF OUR DAD
LIKED LINDA RONSTADT ?

24:11.650 --> 24:13.470
AS A MATTER
OF FACT I DO.

24:13.580 --> 24:16.572
WHEN I CLEANED OUT
HIS RECORD COLLECTION,

24:16.680 --> 24:19.740
THERE WAS A COPY OF
"HEART LIKE A WHEEL" IN IT.

24:22.120 --> 24:23.724
HERE ARE
THE TEACUPS.

24:23.830 --> 24:25.388
AND THESE
ARE DINNER PLATES.

24:25.490 --> 24:27.253
AND THOSE UP THERE
ARE FOR CASSEROLES.

24:27.360 --> 24:29.658
AND THESE ARE
THE CEREAL BOWLS.

24:29.760 --> 24:32.422
PLEASE FEEL FREE
TO USE ANY OF THE DISHES.

24:32.530 --> 24:35.363
IS THERE ONE
I SHOULDN'T USE ?

24:35.470 --> 24:37.506
IT'S SILLY.

24:37.610 --> 24:39.362
THAT ONE USED TO BE
DAVID'S SPECIAL YELLOW BOWL.

24:39.470 --> 24:41.301
HE WOULD GET UPSET
WHEN ANYONE ELSE USED IT.

24:41.410 --> 24:43.776
BUT I'M SURE
HE WON'T MIND ANYMORE.

24:43.880 --> 24:45.677
LET'S NOT
TAKE THE CHANCE.

24:45.780 --> 24:47.873
WE'LL KEEP IT
OUT OF ROTATION.

24:47.980 --> 24:49.311
THANK YOU.

24:49.420 --> 24:52.583
NOW, YOU SEE
THE CHART I MADE ?

24:52.690 --> 24:55.215
EACH MEAL TIME IS
DIVIDED INTO TWO SHIFTS.

24:55.320 --> 24:56.548
ONE FOR EACH OF US.

24:56.660 --> 24:58.628
SO, WE NEVER HAVE
TO SUFFER THE AWKWARDNESS

24:58.730 --> 25:01.028
OF BOTH EATING
AT THE SAME TIME.

25:01.130 --> 25:02.154
THANK YOU.

25:02.260 --> 25:03.454
THAT'S VERY
THOUGHTFUL.

25:03.570 --> 25:05.322
WE JUST SIGN UP EACH DAY
FOR THE ONE WE WANT.

25:05.430 --> 25:08.661
SO, MY DINNER CAN
BE FROM SIX TO SEVEN.

25:08.770 --> 25:11.136
OR FROM
SEVEN TO EIGHT.

25:11.240 --> 25:12.434
EXACTLY.

25:12.540 --> 25:13.973
WHICH DO YOU
WANT TONIGHT ?

25:14.080 --> 25:16.105
I'LL TAKE SEVEN.

25:16.210 --> 25:19.043
ACTUALLY,

25:19.150 --> 25:22.176
I'LL TAKE SIX.

25:22.280 --> 25:23.986
OH GOOD, I HAD
A LATE LUNCH.

25:24.090 --> 25:26.240
JUST USE THAT PEN THERE
TO INITIAL IT.

25:26.350 --> 25:28.386
OF COURSE, OTHER PEOPLE
IN THIS HOUSE

25:28.490 --> 25:30.412
OBVIOUSLY ALSO
USE THE KITCHEN.

25:30.520 --> 25:32.659
IF YOU WANT TO MAKE
A SCHEDULE WITH THEM TOO,

25:32.760 --> 25:34.318
FEEL FREE
TO USE MY SYSTEM.

25:34.430 --> 25:36.921
LAUNDRY FACILITIES
ARE IN HERE.

25:37.030 --> 25:40.761
NOW, SUNDAY NIGHTS
ARE OFF LIMITS TO YOU.

25:40.870 --> 25:43.031
I'M VERY SORRY, BUT THAT'S
WHEN I DO MY LINENS.

25:43.140 --> 25:44.266
YES, MA'AM.

25:44.370 --> 25:46.509
I UNDERSTAND
COMPLETELY.

25:46.610 --> 25:48.771
I SHOULD WRITE
DOWN THAT PART

25:48.880 --> 25:51.769
ABOUT NEVER AIMING THE SHOWER
HEAD AT THAT PART OF THE TILE...

25:51.880 --> 25:53.108
NO NEED.

25:53.210 --> 25:54.973
IT'S ALL IN THE LITTLE BKLET
THAT'S HANGING BY THE SINK.

25:55.080 --> 25:56.638
WHAT A LOVELY ROOM.

25:56.750 --> 25:59.048
SUCH WARM LIGHT.

25:59.150 --> 26:00.651
IT DOES THE TRICK.

26:00.760 --> 26:06.187
"THE SECOND DRAWER STICKS
UNLESS YOU LII-T AS YOU PULL."

26:11.630 --> 26:13.291
THANK YOU.

26:13.400 --> 26:16.039
THAT'S VERY KIND.

26:16.140 --> 26:19.303
ALRIGHT THEN.

26:19.410 --> 26:21.401
THAT'S THE END
OF THE TOUR.

26:21.510 --> 26:23.944
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN NOW.

26:24.050 --> 26:26.006
THANK YOU.

26:56.240 --> 26:57.901
( door closing )

27:00.150 --> 27:02.209
NATE ?

27:05.690 --> 27:08.011
OH, MY GOD.

27:10.660 --> 27:11.922
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE ?

27:12.030 --> 27:13.554
I SHOULD HAVE
CALLED FIRST.

27:13.660 --> 27:15.855
I WAS AFRAID
YOU WOULD...

27:15.960 --> 27:19.726
I NEED TO
TALK TO YOU.

27:19.830 --> 27:23.334
IT WON'T TAKE LONG.

27:25.110 --> 27:28.932
I WOULDN'T ASK YOU
IF IT WASN'T IMPORTANT...

27:29.810 --> 27:31.004
I DON'T KNOW.

27:31.110 --> 27:32.748
I'VE GOT A LOT OF ERRANDS
I HAVE TO RUN TODAY.

27:32.850 --> 27:37.275
UH, CAN I
COME WITH YOU ?

27:39.550 --> 27:41.654
PLEASE ?

27:46.390 --> 27:50.121
IT SEEMS LIKE I JUST GOT THIS
THING SMOG CHECKED LAST MONTH.

27:57.400 --> 28:00.403
YOU KNOW, I CALLED YOU WHEN
I FIRST GOT BACK INTO TOWN...

28:00.510 --> 28:02.375
A COUPLE OF
MONTHS AGO ?

28:02.480 --> 28:04.971
AND I HUNG UP
WHEN YOU ANSWERED.

28:05.080 --> 28:10.712
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE SURE
THAT YOU WERE ALIVE.

28:12.390 --> 28:14.415
I'M SORRY,
IT'S JUST...

28:14.520 --> 28:16.112
AI-TER EVERYTHING
WE WENT THROUGH,

28:16.220 --> 28:18.450
TO NOT EVEN KNOW
IF YOU'RE ALIVE ?

28:18.560 --> 28:20.152
THAT'S...

28:20.260 --> 28:22.421
SAD.

28:23.900 --> 28:28.234
BUT APPARENTLY YOUR SURGERY
WAS A SUCCESS, RIGHT ?

28:28.340 --> 28:29.329
YEAH.

28:29.440 --> 28:34.036
WELL, THE A.V.M. RUPTURED
IN THE MIDDLE OF IT,

28:34.140 --> 28:36.233
AND ALL HELL BROKE LOOSE,
BUT THEY...

28:36.340 --> 28:38.205
FIXED IT.

28:38.310 --> 28:40.278
OH, THANK GOD.

28:42.780 --> 28:44.611
USE YOUR FUCKING
SIGNAL, WOMAN !

28:44.720 --> 28:47.848
YOU CAN
GO UP MY ASS !

28:48.820 --> 28:52.028
( radio playing )

28:54.030 --> 28:55.292
CLAIRE,

28:55.400 --> 28:59.769
I ONCE HAD AN AFFAIR
WITH AN OLDER MARRIED WOMAN.

28:59.870 --> 29:02.464
HER NAME WAS ASTRA.

29:02.570 --> 29:05.767
THAT MEANS STAR,
DID YOU KNOW THAT ?

29:07.670 --> 29:10.036
HAVE YOU EVER
COMMITTED INFIDELITY ?

29:10.140 --> 29:12.040
NO, NOT YET.

29:12.150 --> 29:15.119
BUT SOMEDAY,
HOPEFULLY.

29:15.220 --> 29:16.642
INFIDELITY IS
NOT FUNNY, CLAIRE.

29:16.750 --> 29:17.910
IT'S TRAGIC.

29:18.020 --> 29:19.715
ALL BETRAYAL
IS TRAGIC.

29:19.820 --> 29:23.312
I WAS 21 WHEN
WE FIRST MET.

29:23.420 --> 29:27.550
THE RADIO WAS PLAYING
"I WEAR MY SUNGLASSES AT NIGHT".

29:27.660 --> 29:31.460
SUCH AN INSIPID SONG,

29:33.370 --> 29:36.066
BUT NOW IT ALWAYS
MAKES MY HEART FEEL...

29:36.170 --> 29:39.765
SQUISHED.

29:43.010 --> 29:45.274
AW, SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

29:45.380 --> 29:46.506
YEAH...

29:46.610 --> 29:50.842
SHE'S THE BEST FUCKING THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED TO ME.

29:54.090 --> 29:56.513
SO, WHAT'S GOING
ON WITH YOU ?

29:56.620 --> 29:58.554
OH...

29:58.660 --> 30:01.595
I WENT TO SANTA FE
FOR A WHILE.

30:01.700 --> 30:04.066
I WAS IN
AUSTIN, TEXAS.

30:04.170 --> 30:06.889
